23. cuncta terrarum subacta] It is probable that Pollio had given a stin-ing account of Caesar's African campaign, in which he himself served, and that his description had made a great impression upon Horace. The victory of Thapsus, B. c. 46, made Caesar master of the whole Roman world. ‘ Cuncta terrarum ' is equivalent to ‘ cunctas terras.’
